Citation.sTitle: Thermodynamic Study of LiClO4 Activity Coefficients in Aqueous Solution at (288.15, 298.15, and 308.18) K
Citation.sAbstract: The use of various materials of the electrolyte in a lithium-ion battery must be studied under stable electrochemical conditions, Therefore, the LiClO4 activity coefficients in water at temperatures of (288.15, 298.15 and 308.15) K from emf measurements of the following electrochemical cell without transference containing two ion selective electrodes (ISE): Na-ISE | LiClO4 (m) | ClO4-ISE For this study the molality m varied between c.a 0.007 and 4 mol kg-1.
